        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="990" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d990">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 990<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Military Attaché in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KBGAAJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kessler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">
                            <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Department</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d990fn1">Received by the United States Delegation to the
                        Berlin Conference on July 25 as a retransmission from the <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-24">24 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>667. For <gloss target="#t_ComGenAir1">ComGenAir</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_MilID1">MilID</gloss> Washington D. C.</p>
                <p>Russian Delegation here conducted survey of interned German aircraft presumably
                    those coining here from German Soviet front. Russians propose to fly these out
                    shortly as <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty. Their plans have been
                    publicized in newspapers. See my 591 of 26 June and your 28542 of 7 July.<note n="2" xml:id="d990fn2">Neither printed.</note> Newspapers also carried item
                    that neither <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> or US have made request
                    concerning remainder.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KBGAAJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kessler</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
